          <p class="text-3xl font-bold text-accent-400">$800–$2,400</p>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm font-semibold text-white">Annual paper &amp; printing cost</p>
          <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-gray-400">Paper, toner, printer maintenance, and file storage for a mid-size studio. Digital waivers eliminate this entirely.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-xl border border-ink-800 bg-ink-900/50 p-6">
          <p class="text-3xl font-bold text-accent-400">~80%</p>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm font-semibold text-white">Faster check-in with QR</p>
          <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-gray-400">Paper: 4-6 min per client (find, fill, scan, file). Digital QR: ~30 seconds. For 20 clients/day, that's 1.5+ hours saved.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-xl border border-ink-800 bg-ink-900/50 p-6">
          <p class="text-3xl font-bold text-accent-400">2.5x</p>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm font-semibold text-white">Risk of lost paper waivers</p>
          <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-gray-400">[placeholder for real data — industry estimate: paper waivers are 2-3x more likely to be lost or damaged than cloud-stored digital copies]</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-8 text-center">
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-500">Paper vs digital cost analysis based on industry benchmarks for mid-size tattoo studios (3-5 artists, ~20 clients/day per artist). Your mileage may vary.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

