          <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-gray-400">Electronic signatures on InkFlow carry the same legal weight as handwritten signatures under federal (ESIGN) and state (UETA) law. Each signature record includes: precise timestamp, IP address with geolocation, device fingerprint (browser + OS + screen), SHA-256 hash of the signed document.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-lg border border-ink-800 bg-ink-900/50 p-5">
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-white">✅ Court-Admissible (Not Just a Checkbox)</h3>
          <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-gray-400">Most digital waiver tools produce a "click-wrap" record — practically worthless in court. InkFlow generates a forensic-grade PDF with full electronic evidence chain. Courts have accepted SHA-256 verified digital signatures as superior to paper originals.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-lg border border-ink-800 bg-ink-900/50 p-5">
